The follows the resignation of Lungisa Fuzile after the Cabinet reshuffle which saw the removal of Pravin Gordhan as Finance Minister. CAPE TOWN - It has been announced that Cabinet has appointed Dondo Mogajane as director general of National Treasury in a permanent capacity.Mogajane has been the acting director general since May.The follows the resignation of Lungisa Fuzile after the Cabinet reshuffle which saw the removal of Pravin Gordhan as Finance Minister.Mogajane has worked for the Finance Department since 1999 and was most recently the deputy director-general responsible for public finance.More details to follow.